Executive Profile
Mark C. Vadon  Independent Director, The Home Depot, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 6 Board Members in 6 different organizations across 8 different industries.See Board Relationships47$290,000
Background

		Mr. Mark C. Vadon co-founded Blue Nile Inc. and also served as its Chief Executive Officer from March 18, 1999 to February 2008 and President from March 18, 1999 to February 12, 2007. Mr. Vadon served as Executive Chairman of Blue Nile Inc. from February 7, 2008 to December 31, 2013. Mr. Vadon served as a Sector Advisor at Maveron LLC. He served as a Consultant of Bain & Company from December 1992 to March 1999. He serves as the Chairman of the Board of Chewy.com, LLC. ... He served as the Chairman of zulily, LLC from October 2009 to September 2015. He served as Chairman of Blue Nile Inc. from March 18, 1999 to February 7, 2008. He served as the Chairman of CitizenHawk, Inc. He has been an Independent Director of The Home Depot, Inc. since September 21, 2012 and QVC Group since October 2015 and Liberty Interactive Corporation since October 1, 2015. He has been a Director of zulily, llc since October 2009. He is a Director of Home Depot U.S.A., Inc. He serves on the Board of Wine.com. He served as a Director of Blue Nile Inc. from March 18, 1999 to December 31, 2013. He served as a Director of CitizenHawk, Inc. Mr. Vadon holds a BA in Social Studies from Harvard University and an MBA from the Stanford University.Read Full Background




